{"lemma":"ذَكَرُ","slug":"ذَكَرُ","root":"ذ.ك.ر","root_slug":"ذ-ك-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ك-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ذَكَر","root":"ذكر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":18},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":20},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13923","n13924","n13925","n13926","n13927","n13928"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mention","examples":[{"text":"فَإِذَا أُنْزِلَتْ سُورَةٌ مُحْكَمَةٌ وَذُكِرَ فِيهَا الْقِتَالُ رَأَيْتَ الَّذِينَ فِي قُلُوبِهِم مَرَضٌ يَنظُرُونَ إِلَيْكَ نَظَرَ الْمَغْشِيِّ عَلَيْهِ مِنَ الْمَوْتِ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to remember, to recall"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bear in mind"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to think"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to speak, to talk"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to state, to designate, to indicate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to refer"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to report, to tell, to relate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to remind, to point out"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ذَكَرَ (ḏakara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"recollection, remembrance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reputation, renown"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mentioning, quoting, quote, citing, citation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stating, indicating, naming"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"report, account, narration"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dhikr, zikr"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"male","tags":["masculine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"penis"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make masculine"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pollinate artificially"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Akkadian 𒈬 (zakārum, “to name, to mention”), Hebrew זָכַר (zachár, “to remember”) and Ugaritic 𐎏𐎋𐎗 (ḏkr, “to remember”).\n\nCognate with Hebrew זֵכֶר (zécher, “remembrance”).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *ðikar- (“man; male; phallus”). Cognate with Hebrew זָכָר (zachár, “male”)."},"ipa":["/ða.ka.ra/","/ðak.ka.ra/","/ðikr/","/ða.kar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13923","headword_ar":"ذَكْرٌ","root":"*kr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akiyrN","text_ar":"ذَكِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13924","headword_ar":"ذُكْرٌ","root":"*kr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofN *uw *ukorK","text_ar":"سَيْفٌ ذُو ذُكْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukurK","text_ar":"ذُكُرٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in different copies of the S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*okirapK","text_ar":"اَذْكِرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is the pl.,] (A,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cutting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp, sword."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukorapN","text_ar":"ذُكْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["A"]},{"entry_id":"n13925","headword_ar":"ذِكْرٌ","root":"*kr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(Yoo, A'Obeyd, Yaakoob, S, M, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukorN","text_ar":"ذُكْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yoo, A'Obeyd, Yaakoob, S, A, Msb, K, TA,) or the latter only in the first of the senses here to be explained, (Fr, Msb, TA,) and the latter only is mentioned in this sense in the Fs, (TA,) and is said by El-Ahmar to be of the dial. of Kureysh, (TA,) [both said in the Msb to be simple substs., though many hold them to be inf. ns.,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akorN","text_ar":"ذَكْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to one of the expositors of the Fs, but this is strange, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorapN","text_ar":"ذِكْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukorapN","text_ar":"ذُكْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikoraY","text_ar":"ذِكْرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, [see 1, first sentence,]) and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dikorN","text_ar":"دِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dukorN","text_ar":"دُكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by ISd as of the dial. of Rabee'ah, but held by him to be of weak authority, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Remembrance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K, &c.;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"presence"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib:) also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN biAlqalobi","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ بِالقَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) to distinguish it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in another sense, to be explained below: (TA:) he pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorapN","text_ar":"ذِكْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikarN","text_ar":"ذِكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) also said to be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikoraY","text_ar":"ذِكْرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHd","text_ar":"احد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijoEalohu minoka EalaY *ukorK","text_ar":"اِجْعَلْهُ مِنْكَ عَلَى ذُكْرٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorK","text_ar":"ذِكْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the same sense,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Place thou him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in thy remembrance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajoEalahu min~iY","text_ar":"اَجْعَلَهُ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY *ukorK","text_ar":"عَلَى ذُكْرٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorK","text_ar":"ذِكْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not forget him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zaAla min~iY EalaY *ukorK","text_ar":"مَا زَالَ مِنِّى عَلَى ذُكْرٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorK","text_ar":"ذِكْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or the former only, (Fr, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, did not cease to be in my remembrance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not forget him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota min~iY EalaY *ukorK","text_ar":"اَنْتَ مِنِّى عَلَى ذُكْرٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art in my mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, Lb.) ―         -b2-  The words in the Kur [xxix. 44]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wala*ikoru A@ll~`hi A^akobaru","text_ar":"وَلَذِكْرُ ا@للّٰهِ اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"admit of two explanations:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The remembrance of God is better"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a man than a man's remembrance of a man: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the remembrance of God is better"},{"kind":"text","text":"as more efficacious in forbidding evil conduct than is prayer. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Memory; a certain quality of the mind, by which a man is able to remember what he cares to know;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HifuZN","text_ar":"حِفُظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", except that this latter term is used with regard to the preservation of a thing [in the mind], whereas the former is used with regard to calling it to mind. (Er-Rághib.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, Msb, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukorN","text_ar":"ذُكْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) or the former only accord. to Fr, (Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikoraY","text_ar":"ذِكْرَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mention, telling, relating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: said by some to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SamotN","text_ar":"صَمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN biAll~isaAni","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ بِاللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) to distinguish it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense first explained above. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"praise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glorification, of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"celebration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declaration, of his remoteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freedom, from every impurity"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperfection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from everything derogatory from his glory;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamodu lil~`hi","text_ar":"الحَمْدُ لِلّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^all~`hu A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A_ilaAha A_il~aA","text_ar":"لَا اـِلَاهَ اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [&c., see 1,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and uttering all the forms of his praise: a reading,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reciting, of the Kur-án: a thanking"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedience"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Abu-l- 'Abbás:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prayer to God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplication."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás, K.) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Praise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eulogy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of another. (S, * K, * TA.) ―         -b4-  [And, accord. to some, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dispraise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"See 1.] ―         -b5-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is current upon the tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fame; renown; report; reputation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether good or evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukorapN","text_ar":"ذُكْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AZ, ISd, K.) Thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu *ikorN fiY Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"لَهُ ذِكْرٌ فِى النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has fame among the people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which it has also the signification next following. (A.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eminence; nobility; honour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K.) So in the Kur [xciv. 4],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warafaEonaA","text_ar":"وَرَفَعْنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka *ikoraka","text_ar":"لَكَ ذِكْرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And We have raised for thee thine eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy nobility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thine honour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as some say, it means, when I am mentioned, thou art mentioned with Me: and again, in the Kur [xliii. 43],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A_in~ahu la*ikorN laka wa liqawomika","text_ar":"وَ اـِنَّهُ لَذِكْرٌ لَكَ وَ لِقَوْمِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the Kur-án)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is an honour to thee and to thy people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Also, in the Kur [xxxviii. 1],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa AlquroA=ni *iY Al*~ikori","text_ar":"وَ القُرْا=نِ ذِى الذِّكْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By the Kur-án possessed of eminence, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) ―         -b8-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A book containing an exposition of religion, and an institution of religious laws:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any book of the prophets:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and especially the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Kur-án:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taworaApN","text_ar":"تَوْرَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Book of the Law revealed to Moses"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Aboo-Hureyreh, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zbr","text_ar":"زبر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and that ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"law"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recorded"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in heaven."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sa'eed Ibn-Jubeyr, TA ubi suprà.) ―         -b9-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An exhortation; an admonition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a warning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xxxviii. 1.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikoru Haq~K","text_ar":"ذِكْرُ حَقٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A written obligation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sak~N","text_ar":"صَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwru Haq~K","text_ar":"ذُكُورُ حَقٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwru HuquwqK","text_ar":"ذُكُورُ حُقُوقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liY EalaY h`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"لِى عَلَى هٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikoru Haq~K","text_ar":"ذِكْرُ حَقٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have a written obligation to insure this thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)       -A3-  See also the next paragraph, in the latter half."}],"source_refs":["Fr","Msb","TA","S","M","K","MF","A"]},{"entry_id":"n13926","headword_ar":"ذَكَرٌ","root":"*kr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[probably originally signifying “ mentioned, ” or “ talked of, ” of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaDN","text_ar":"نَفَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":970},{"kind":"text","text":"sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manofuwDN","text_ar":"مَنْفُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaTN","text_ar":"خَبَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobuwTN","text_ar":"مَخْبُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDN","text_ar":"قَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqobuwDN","text_ar":"مَقْبُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.; and hence the first, and perhaps most others, of the significations here following:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Male; masculine; of the male,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"masculine, sex,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gender; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unovaY","text_ar":"اُنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, Msb, K, &c.:) [the corresponding word in Hebrew ("},{"kind":"text","text":") has been supposed to have this signification because a male is much “ mentioned, ” or “ talked of; ” and it is well known that the Arabs make comparatively little account of a female:] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwrN","text_ar":"ذُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwrapN","text_ar":"ذُكُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikaArN","text_ar":"ذِكَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikaArapN","text_ar":"ذِكَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukoraAnN","text_ar":"ذُكْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikarapN","text_ar":"ذِكَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) [the last, in one copy of the S, I find written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorapN","text_ar":"ذِكْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, if correct, is a pl. of pauc.: and in the TA, in the same phrase in which it occurs in the S, it is written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukorapN","text_ar":"ذُكْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and expressly said to be with damm, so that it is a quasi-pl. n.:] the pl. form with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not allowable. (Msb.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kami Al*~ikarapu mino","text_ar":"كَمِ الذِّكَرَةُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladika","text_ar":"وَلَدِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~ikorapu","text_ar":"الذِّكْرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~ukorapu","text_ar":"الذُّكْرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, (accord. to the TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How many are the males of thy children?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male organ of generation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"penis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawofN","text_ar":"عَوْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K, &c.;) of a man: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroj","text_ar":"فَرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an equivocal term, but here evidently used in the above-mentioned sense,] of an animal: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwrN","text_ar":"ذُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikarapN","text_ar":"ذِكَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinabapN","text_ar":"عِنَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikaArapN","text_ar":"ذِكَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aAkiyru","text_ar":"مَذَاكِيرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) the last contr. to analogy, (S, Msb,) as though used for the sake of distinction between this signification and the one immediately preceding: (S:) or of the same class as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAsinu","text_ar":"مَحَاسِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with respect to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonN","text_ar":"حُسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAmiHu","text_ar":"مَلَامِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with respect to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamoHapN","text_ar":"لَمْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (ISd:) Akh says that it is a pl. without a [proper] sing., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaAbiydu","text_ar":"عَبَابِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAbiylu","text_ar":"اَبَابِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to the T, it has no sing.; or if it have a sing., it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*okirN","text_ar":"مُذْكِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqodimN","text_ar":"مُقْدِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqaAdiymu","text_ar":"مَقَادِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parts next to the penis:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"penis with what is around it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genitals;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and is similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAriqu","text_ar":"مَفَارِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAbato mafaAriqu","text_ar":"شَابَتْ مَفَارِقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osihi","text_ar":"رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEa ma*aAkiyrahu","text_ar":"قَطَعَ مَذَاكِيرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signified"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He extirpated his penis."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b3-  Applied to a man, (A, K,) it also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong; courageous; acute and ardent; vigorous and effective in affairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stubborn; and disdainful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"masculine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unovaY","text_ar":"اُنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a woman. (T and A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anv","text_ar":"انث"},{"kind":"text","text":".) The signification of “ strong, courageous, and stubborn, ” and the significations which the same word has when applied to rain and to a saying, are assigned in the K to ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikorN","text_ar":"ذِكْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but [SM says,] I know not how this is; for in the other lexicons they are assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarN","text_ar":"ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yafoEaluhu A_il~aA","text_ar":"لَا يَفْعَلُهُ اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwrapu Alr~ijaAli","text_ar":"ذُكُورَةُ الرِّجَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"None will do it but such as are strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b4-  Applied to iron, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of the toughest and best quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and strongest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aniyvN","text_ar":"اَنِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [iron"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"converted into steel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akiyrN","text_ar":"ذَكِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukorapN","text_ar":"ذُكْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-  Applied to a sword, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='","text_ar":"مَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diversified wavy marks, streaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*~ak~arN","text_ar":"مُذَّكَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the edge is of steel"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiydN *akarN","text_ar":"حَدِيدٌ ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maton","text_ar":"مَتْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle of the broad side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of soft iron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which the people say that they are of the fabric of the Jinn, or Genii: (A'Obeyd, S:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ak~aru","text_ar":"مُذَكَّرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a sharp iron blade or edge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As:) the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwrN","text_ar":"ذُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 168.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwru Albuquwli","text_ar":"ذُكُورُ البُقُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Herbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants, that are hard and thick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$obN","text_ar":"عُشْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are thick, and inclining to bitterness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraAruhaA","text_ar":"اَحْرَارُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies such as are slender and sweet: (TA:) or the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are thick and rough."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwrapu AlT~iybi","text_ar":"ذُكُورَةُ الطِّيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwruhu","text_ar":"ذُكُورُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ikaAratuhu","text_ar":"ذِكَارَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perfume proper for men, exclusively of women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that leaves no stain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that becomes dissipated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as musk, and aloes-wood, and camphire, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAliyap","text_ar":"غَالِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ariyrap","text_ar":"ذَرِيرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See the contr.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybN muw^an~avN","text_ar":"طِيبٌ مُوَنَّثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anv","text_ar":"انث"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarN","text_ar":"ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the Kur-án signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eminently excellent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) See 2. ―         -b9-  Applied to a saying, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong and firm:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner to poetry. (A.) ―         -b10-  The Arabs disliked a she-camel's bringing forth a male; and hence they applied the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarN","text_ar":"ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", met., to (tropical:)  Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disliked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b11-  [Thus,] applied to rain, it signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Violent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falling in large drops."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) They said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbati AlA^aroDa *ukuwru AlA^asomiyapi","text_ar":"اَصَابَتِ الاَرْضَ ذُكُورُ الاَسْمِيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rains bringing intense cold and torrents fell upon the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b12-  Applied to a day, (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Severe; distressing; hard to be borne:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ak~arN","text_ar":"مُذَكَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b13-  IDrd says, I think that the name"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*kr","text_ar":"الذكر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TA, without any syll. signs; app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~akaru","text_ar":"الذَّكَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is applied by some of the Arabs to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imaAku Alr~aAmiHu","text_ar":"السِّمَاكُ الرَّامِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or the star"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arcturus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","T","ISd","As"]},{"entry_id":"n13927","headword_ar":"ذَكُرٌ","root":"*kr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akiyrN","text_ar":"ذَكِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13928","headword_ar":"ذَكِرٌ","root":"*kr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akiyrN","text_ar":"ذَكِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}